1. Short-Term
 A. Units
   * Generic Class for a unit
   * Specific units:
     * Unique class for each that inherits from general
     * File that contains the necessary info for each unit, no specific classes
       (already flawed cause some units have different movement types)
   * Unique sub-classes, like for land, air, and sea
 B. Board
   * Zone Class (a square on the board)
 C. Combat
   * Battle class (takes two or more units)
     * Responsible for doing the rolling and moving through the stages 
 D. Movement
   * Breadth-First Search through the zones, starting at a unit's current
     location.  Zones will have to know their neighbors.

2. Long-Term
 A. Animation
 B. Networking
